annotation: The user wants to find the surface area of a solid. The solid is a cube with a quarter-cylinder removed from the top. The side length of the cube is 14.2 cm. The radius of the cylinder is half the side length, which is 7.1 cm. The height/length of the cylinder is equal to the side length of the cube, 14.2 cm.
problem_text_en: Find the solid surface area if the side length is 14.2 and the radius is half that.
